In addition, the number of places suitable for arranging a colony is quite low, and the birds do not have the opportunity to change them. The colony in Banff National Park in Alberta was maintained from at least 1919 to 1993, colonies in California have been used for at least 20 years. managed to find abandoned colonies of the black swift. Individual nests are also used from year to year [29]. However, Marin noted that occasionally the birds change the place for the nest or pair [20].